Your team is building a payment processing system using .NET SDK. An Activity polls an external payment gateway that frequently returns 'payment pending' responses during normal operation. You've implemented it as follows:

```csharp
[Activity]
public async Task<PaymentResult> CheckPaymentStatusAsync(string paymentId)
{
    var status = await paymentGateway.CheckAsync(paymentId);
    if (status == PaymentStatus.Pending)
    {
        throw new ApplicationFailureException(
            "Payment still pending",
            errorType: "PaymentPending");
    }
    return new PaymentResult(status);
}
```

In production, you notice your monitoring dashboards are flooded with ERROR-level Activity failure metrics and alerts firing constantly, even though the system is working correctly. The pending status occurs thousands of times per hour across all payment workflows. What is the most appropriate fix, and what effect will it have on your observability stack?
